    "body": "> [!NOTE]\r\n> This PR I did with assistance from Codex.\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nThe `nvim_get_chan_info()` terminal channel test used `shell-test INTERACT` to verify that `jobstop()` reports an unhandled `SIGHUP` as exit code `129`.\r\n\r\n`INTERACT` reads from stdin with `fgets()`, so closing the PTY could race with `SIGHUP` delivery:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/0e69a380263f5a78d11cd05c65cc224a3c74b53e/test/functional/fixtures/shell-test.c#L133-L155\r\n\r\nIf `fgets()` observed EOF first, `shell-test` exited normally with code `0`, causing intermittent failures on slower sanitizer builds.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nAdd a `shell-test HOLD` mode that prints a readiness prompt and then waits without reading stdin. Use it for the `SIGHUP` assertion so PTY EOF cannot make the helper exit normally before the signal path is observed.\r\n\r\nAI-assisted: Codex\r\n\r\nFixes #39241",
